peech and exchange. The possibilities for failure and slippage reveal people's mutual vulnerabilities and give words and things part of their power. Keane shows how the dilemmas posed by the effort to use and control language and objects are implicated with general problems of power, authority, and agency. He persuades us to look differently at ideas of voice and value. Integrating the analysis of words and things, this book contributes to a wide range of fields, including linguistic anthropology, cultural studies, social theory, and the studies of material culture, art, and political economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnakalang (Indonesian people)xPsychology. 0aAnakalang (Indonesian people)xRites and ceremonies. 0aAnakalang (Indonesian people)xSocial conditions. 0aAnakalang dialectxDiscourse analysis. 0aAnakalang dialectxSemantics. 0aInterpersonal relationsxIndonesiaxSumba Island. 0aInterpersonal relationszIndonesiazSumba Island. 0aRepresentation (Philosophy). 0aSocial structurexIndonesiaxSumba Island. 0aSocial structurezIndonesiazSumba Island. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aagency.  aanakalang.  aart.  aasian history.  aauthority.  aawareness of risk.  aconcrete practices.  acultural studies.  acustoms and traditions.  aethnography.  aindonesia.  aindonesian island.  aindonesian society.  alinguistic anthropology.  alinguistics.  amaterial culture.  apoetic speech.  apolitical economy.  apower of language.  apower.  apublic events.  arepresentation.  arepresentational practices.  aritual exchange.  aritual speech.  asocial existence.  asocial sciences.  asocial theory.  asumba.  atension.  atheoretical discussion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California